    {
      "id": "84ead5ef5e05a92fd08b788184ec1ffdc6313924",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 458,
        "name": "Olaf Faaland",
        "email": "faaland1@llnl.gov",
        "username": "ofaaland"
      },
      "date": "2016-03-22 16:57:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHello Alex,\n\nThanks for the review.  This patch is not a duplicate, just related.\n\ndmu_objset_disown(od_os) is currently called in three places.  One is osd_objset_open(), which http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/15671/ fixed.\n\nHowever, when osd_objset_open() fails it sets od_os to NULL before returning to osd_mount().  osd_mount() then ends up in its error handling/cleanup code block.  This patch prevents osd_mount() from calling dmu_objset_disown(NULL), in that block.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2a552f5cae76c1a18aeae66578398227685367a0",
      "author": {
